ography and proceeding to early twenty-first-century drama, this project examines performances of blackness’s deadpan aesthetic within and beyond black embodiments, including Young Jean Lee’s The Shipment and Branden Jacobs-Jenkins’s Neighbors, as well as Buster Keaton’s signature character and Steve McQueen’s restitution of the former’s legacy within the continuum of Black cultural production. Through this varied archive, Post reveals how deadpan aesthetics function in and between opacity and fugitivity, minimalism and saturation, excess and insensibility.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAesthetics. 0aBlack peoplexRace identity. 0aBody language. 0aFacial expression. 7aART / Performance.2bisacsh  aAesthetics.  aAnthropomorphism.  aAwayness.  aBlackness.  aDeadpan.  aEmpiricism.  aExcess.  aFaçade.  aFugitivity.  aIndestructability.  aInexpression.  aInsentience.  aKeaton.  aLooming.  aMcQueen.  aMinimalism.  aMinstrel.  aModernity.  aMonochrome.  aObjecthood.  aObscurity.  aOpacity.  aPortraiture.  aRespectability.  aRiddle.  aSheerness.  aSpecimen.  aStereotype.  aSubjectivity.  aTheatrical.  aThreat.  aTransparency.  aaffect.  agesture.  aperformance.  aresistance.  avisuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2023z9783111318103oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2023 Englishz978311131903208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075163540uhttps://doi.org/10.18